{"bill":{"bill_id":1639580,"change_hash":"c79a70bb367a4ad49a0c78f8b27c3f12","session_id":1988,"session":{"session_id":1988,"state_id":46,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/VA\/bill\/SB821\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/lis.virginia.gov\/cgi-bin\/legp604.exe?231+sum+SB821","completed":0,"status":2,"status_date":"2023-01-23","progress":[{"date":"2022-12-20","event":1},{"date":"2022-12-20","event":9},{"date":"2023-01-19","event":10},{"date":"2023-01-23","event":2},{"date":"2023-02-10","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-13","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-16","event":2}],"state":"VA","state_id":46,"bill_number":"SB821","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"S","body_id":8,"current_body":"S","current_body_id":8,"title":"Arrests, certain, and convictions of certain individuals; reports to division superintendents.","description":"Reports of certain arrests and convictions of certain Reports of certain arrests and convictions of certain individuals to division superintendents; employment verification; method of submission; compilation. Requires each division superintendent to identify, update as necessary, and make available to the Department of Education and to other appropriate individuals a fax number, an email address, and a mailing address at which the division superintendent will receive the reports required to be transmitted pursuant to relevant law from (i) every state official or agency and every sheriff, police officer, or other local law-enforcement officer or conservator of the peace having the power to arrest for a felony upon arresting a person who is known or discovered by the arresting official to be a full-time, part-time, permanent, or temporary teacher or any other employee in any local school division in the Commonwealth for a felony or a Class 1 misdemeanor or an equivalent offense in another state and (ii) the clerk of any circuit court or any district court in the Commonwealth upon the conviction of a Board of Education-licensed school employee for certain enumerated felonies. The bill requires the Department to compile and make publicly available on its website a list of such fax numbers, email addresses, and mailing addresses. The bill also requires all such arresting officials or agencies and all such clerks to transmit the required reports via certified mail, return receipt requested, or to the identified fax numbers and email addresses. The bill finally requires, until July 1, 2027, all such arresting officials or agencies request in writing that the Virginia Employment Commission provide the name of the current employer of each arrested person for purposes of determining whether such notice is required.","pending_committee_id":0,"committee":[],"referrals":[{"date":"2022-12-20","committee_id":163,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Education and Health"},{"date":"2023-01-11","committee_id":3893,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Education: Public Education"},{"date":"2023-02-10","committee_id":151,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Education"}],"history":[{"date":"2022-12-20","action":"Prefiled and ordered printed; offered 01\/11\/23 23100637D","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":0},{"date":"2022-12-20","action":"Referred to Committee on Education and Health","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-11","action":"Assigned Education sub: Public Education","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-19","action":"Reported from Education and Health (15-Y 0-N)","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-20","action":"Constitutional reading dispensed (38-Y 0-N)","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-23","action":"Read second time and engrossed","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-24","action":"Read third time and pas